article.headline: Northwestern 85, Northwestern State 59
article.story: EVANSTON, Ill. (AP) -- Kevin Coble scored 19 points to lead Northwestern to an 85-59 victory over Northwestern State on Sunday. Tim Doyle had nine assists for the Wildcats (10-3), who shot 73 percent from the field in taking a 53-29 halftime lead. Luke Rogers led the Demons (5-7) with 17 points and six rebounds. Keithan Hancock added 14 points and Gerrell Thomas had 13 for Northwestern State. Craig Moore and Jason Okrzesik each added 13 points for the Wildcats, which shot 63 percent from the field overall. The Demons shot 36.4 percent from the field.
